title: Free geology presentation set for Thursday
title_page: Free geology presentation set for Thursday
maintext:
ELLENSBURG — A free geology presentation focused on northeast Washington is planned at 7 p.m Thursday in the new Central Washington University Science Building II, Room 103, according to a news release.
Andy Buddington of Spokane Community College will give a presentation titled, “Unroofing the ancient Precambrian basement in the Priest River complex of northeast Washington.”
The Priest River complex is one of several Inland Northwest metamorphic core complexes that formed during Eocene time due to crustal extension and unroofing. Here, metamorphic rocks of the middle crust, including Precambrian basement as old as 2.6 billion years, are exposed. Buddington will discuss the geology and development of the complex along with glimpses of the poorly-known Precambrian basement history for this part of the North American continent.
The lecture is sponsored by the Ellensburg Chapter of the Ice Age Floods Institute.
